      • checkIfMatch

        private java.lang.String checkIfMatch(DataPort referencePort,
                                      InputPort portToMatch)
        Checks if the given input port matches the specified reference port. Match criteria is the data type. The reference port must have a data type that is equal to a type of one of the given ports or it must have a super type.
        Parameters:
        referencePort -
        portToMatch -
        Returns:
        null if match, port captions otherwise
